blog.description: The rants of a pop culture fiend  - Header gif created by the uber talented @peggyswilliams

body:
My husband just informed me…

…that the latest argument tearing the internet apart is: Who is the best cinematic Spider-man:

  1. Tobey Maguire
  2. Andrew Garfield
  3. Tom Holland

My response?

Well, this is the easiest test I’ve ever taken, the answer is 3, Tom Holland.

My husband was all: No, but some people think that the other two were good.

And I was like: Well, those people are wrong, because the answer is 3, Tom Holland.

title: Murder by Machine
body:
Spider-Man UK Annual 1981

Cute story. But nothing much is explained.

  • Villain Attacks Hero? Yup. It’s just an attack on Spider-Man. And the script doesn’t bother to tell us who or why.
  • Most of it is just Spidey trapped in a room easily avoiding/escaping three attempts to kill him.
  • The ending is cute, however, and does provoke a small chuckle.

5/10
